Act as a Grade 1 English teacher. Using only the vocabulary list provided, write simple, kid-friendly definitions suitable for 6–7-year-old students.
Requirements:
Use very simple words.
Keep each definition short (one short sentence).
Do not use the word itself in the definition.
Make definitions concrete and easy to understand.
Format exactly like this:
word, definition
Put each word and its definition on one line.
Do not add extra explanations or blank lines.
